data.description: Owner is offering a GENEROUS 10k closing cost credit that can be used for CLOSING COSTS OR RATE BUY DOWN!! Enjoy a lower monthly payment and long term savings with a rate buy down. A Classic Gem Restored: Welcome home to 108 Douglas Heights. A beautifully renovated home, where you'll find original hardwoods, stained glass windows, and the perfect marriage of vintage accents and modern upgrades. This 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom bungalow stands as a testament to meticulous renovation. With around 2300 square feet, in addition to its 4 beds & 3 full baths, this 2 story home also offers a foyer/living space upon entering, a formal dining room, large kitchen, sunroom, master on main, large closets, 2 fireplaces, and a vast, fenced backyard with a fire pit to enjoy. There is no lack of detail to be found in this home. Once inside, the coffered ceiling, elegant chandelier, and fire place will immediately steal your attention. To your right is 1 of 2 downstairs bedrooms. To your left, through the french doors is the grand formal dining room. The stained glass windows above the built in buffet are a homeowners dream. The dining room also features a white washed ventless gas fire place and a convenient entrance to the kitchen. The kitchen features granite counter tops, soft close cabinets, an island, stainless steels appliances, and plenty of electrical outlets for additional countertop appliances. Just past the kitchen is the hall bath and laundry room. Your guests will surely be wowed by the lovingly restored 1920's claw foot bathtub. At the rear of the home is the sun-soaked sun room. This room speaks for itself with its abundance of windows, space, and views overlooking the back yard. Just down the hallway is the master suite. You will appreciate the generous closet size and especially the master bathroom. It has a double vanity, granite countertops, beautifully tiled shower, sliding glass door, bluetooth/LED fixture and is sure to be a place you look forward to getting ready in. Once upstairs, you discover the two final bedrooms. One with windows overlooking the distinct uniqueness of Douglas Heights and the other with a walk in closet and a bathroom spacious enough to make anyone jealous. Of course the outside of the home also offers many desirable features. Fresh landscaping, a fenced yard around the back of the .42 acre lot, fire pit, a concrete slab ready and wired for an out building, shade trees, privacy, and plenty of space for a garden or outdoor activities. The roof and HVAC were installed in 2017, new hot water heater installed in 2023, electrical & plumbing completely replaced in 2023. Don't let this home slip through your fingers. Call to schedule your tour to see all that this home has to offer in person!
